{{afc comment|1=trimming these off. the parameter works as "burial" so no need to use "burial"[[User:Immanuelle|Immanuelle]] ([[User talk:Immanuelle|talk]]) 03:35, 28 March 2025 (UTC)}} {{afc comment|1=added parameters Interred_individual and Mausoleum is planned to be added but I messed up in template editing[[User:Immanuelle|Immanuelle]] ([[User talk:Immanuelle|talk]]) 02:40, 28 March 2025 (UTC)}} {{afc comment|1=now we have a 'burial' and 'burial goods' parameter. So a lot of these pages might not be marked on our wiki as having unknown parameters. But specifically keeping this comment here in case of import, these parameters should be added to [[Template:infobox ancient site]] rather than deleted from this draft or article[[User:Immanuelle|Immanuelle]] ([[User talk:Immanuelle|talk]]) 02:01, 28 March 2025 (UTC)}} {{afc comment|1=I hope this is not too annoying but this article is gonna be placed under [[:Category:Pages using infobox ancient site with unknown parameters]] and there is a decent chance these unknown parameters are ones I want added to the main template like burial chamber structure and burial goods. Please do not use any bots that just remove the unknown parameters without looking at them. This was added through [[Special:MassEditRegex]] to all pages with the category so apologies if it was just some kind of an error like the image parameter being in Japanese[[User:Immanuelle|Immanuelle]] ([[User talk:Immanuelle|talk]]) 06:00, 27 March 2025 (UTC)}}
{{Multiple Issues | Refs Needed = June 2023 | Single Source = June 2023 }} {{Infobox ancient site|type = [[Zenpokoenfun]] |name = Kōshinzuka Kofun |image = [[File:庚申塚古墳１.jpg|250px|Full view of Kōshinzuka Kofun]] |location = {{ill|Nagano Prefecture|ja|長野県|12=draft}}{{ill|Iizuna Town|ja|飯綱町|12=draft}} Hirade, Nishinura 1007-1, 1008-1 |location = {{coord|36|43|22|N|138|15|01|E|map_size:20000}} |type = {{ill|Keyhole-shaped Kofun|ja|前方後円墳|1=Zenpokoenfun|12=draft}} |built = Early {{ill|5th century|ja|5世紀|12=draft}} |area = Total length: approx. 52m; Rear circle diameter: approx. 31m |Buried Person = Unknown |burial goods = Gri11ed {{ill|Haniwa|ja|埴輪|12=draft}} ({{ill|Cylindrical Haniwa|ja|円筒埴輪|1=Cylindrical Haniwa|12=draft}}) |Historic Site designation1 = Town (typeerly village) Historic Site1 in [[1980]] (Showa 55) }} '''Kōshinzuka Kofun''' (庚申塚古墳) is a {{ill|Keyhole-shaped Kofun|ja|前方後円墳|1=Zenpokoenfun|12=draft}} located in {{ill|Iizuna Town|ja|飯綱町|12=draft}}, {{ill|Nagano Prefecture|ja|長野県|12=draft}}.
The mound is named "Kōshinzuka" because an ancient {{ill|Kōshin-tō|ja|庚申塔|12=draft}} was enshrined on it. In [[1933]] (Showa 8), Eiji Kuriiwa conducted an investigation and identified the site as a keyhole-shaped Kofun.
The mound, believed to have been constructed in the early {{ill|5th century|ja|5世紀|12=draft}}, yielded burial goods including gri11ed {{ill|Haniwa|ja|埴輪|12=draft}} (cylindrical Haniwa), marking it as the sixth example of such finds in Japan.
== Overview ==
* type: {{ill|Keyhole-shaped Kofun|ja|前方後円墳|1=Zenpokoenfun|12=draft}} * area: ** Total length: approx. 52m ** Rear circle diameter: approx. 31m ** Rear circle height: 3.5m ** Front projection width: approx. 15–17m ** Front projection height: 1.5m
<gallery widths="200px"> 庚申塚古墳２.jpg|Close view of Kōshinzuka Kofun 庚申塚古墳３.jpg|Stone monument 庚申塚古墳４.jpg|Kōshin-tō </gallery>
== location ==
* Nagano Prefecture, Kamiminochi District, {{ill|Iizuna Town|ja|飯綱町|12=draft}}, Hirade, Nishinura 1007-1, 1008-1
== Transportation Access ==
* Nearest Station: {{ill|Shinano Railway|ja|しなの鉄道|12=draft}} {{ill|Mure Station|ja|牟礼駅|12=draft}} (Approx. 8 minutes by car)
== References ==
* Mure Village History and School History Compilation Committee, *Mure Village History* (Vol. 1), pp. 419–420, 817. == See Also ==
* {{ill|Tankakyō|ja|丹霞郷|12=draft}} * {{ill|List of Kofuns in Japan|ja|日本の古墳一覧|12=draft}}
{{Japanese-history-stub}}
