{{Multiple Issues | Refs Needed = June 2023 | Single Source = June 2023 }} {{Infobox ancient site|type = [[Zenpokoenfun]] |name = Kōshinzuka Kofun |image = [[File:庚申塚古墳１.jpg|250px|Full view of Kōshinzuka Kofun]] |location = {{ill|Nagano Prefecture|ja|長野県|12=draft}}{{ill|Iizuna Town|ja|飯綱町|12=draft}} Hirade, Nishinura 1007-1, 1008-1 |location = {{coord|36|43|22|N|138|15|01|E|map_size:20000}} |type = {{ill|Keyhole-shaped Kofun|ja|前方後円墳|1=Zenpokoenfun|1=Zenpokoenfun|12=draft}} |built = Early {{ill|5th century|ja|5世紀|12=draft}} |area = Total length: approx. 52m; Rear circle diameter: approx. 31m |Buried Person = Unknown |burial goods = Gri11ed {{ill|Haniwa|ja|埴輪|12=draft}} ({{ill|Cylindrical Haniwa|ja|円筒埴輪|1=Cylindrical Haniwa|12=draft}}) |Historic Site designation1 = Town (typeerly village) Historic Site1 in [[1980]] (Showa 55) }} '''Kōshinzuka Kofun''' (庚申塚古墳) is a {{ill|Keyhole-shaped Kofun|ja|前方後円墳|1=Zenpokoenfun|1=Zenpokoenfun|12=draft}} located in {{ill|Iizuna Town|ja|飯綱町|12=draft}}, {{ill|Nagano Prefecture|ja|長野県|12=draft}}.
The mound is named "Kōshinzuka" because an ancient {{ill|Kōshin-tō|ja|庚申塔|12=draft}} was enshrined on it. In [[1933]] (Showa 8), Eiji Kuriiwa conducted an investigation and identified the site as a keyhole-shaped Kofun.
The mound, believed to have been constructed in the early {{ill|5th century|ja|5世紀|12=draft}}, yielded burial goods including gri11ed {{ill|Haniwa|ja|埴輪|12=draft}} (cylindrical Haniwa), marking it as the sixth example of such finds in Japan.
== Overview ==
* type: {{ill|Keyhole-shaped Kofun|ja|前方後円墳|1=Zenpokoenfun|1=Zenpokoenfun|12=draft}} * area: ** Total length: approx. 52m ** Rear circle diameter: approx. 31m ** Rear circle height: 3.5m ** Front projection width: approx. 15–17m ** Front projection height: 1.5m
<gallery widths="200px"> 庚申塚古墳２.jpg|Close view of Kōshinzuka Kofun 庚申塚古墳３.jpg|Stone monument 庚申塚古墳４.jpg|Kōshin-tō </gallery>
== location ==
* Nagano Prefecture, Kamiminochi District, {{ill|Iizuna Town|ja|飯綱町|12=draft}}, Hirade, Nishinura 1007-1, 1008-1
== Transportation Access ==
* Nearest Station: {{ill|Shinano Railway|ja|しなの鉄道|12=draft}} {{ill|Mure Station|ja|牟礼駅|12=draft}} (Approx. 8 minutes by car)
== References ==
* Mure Village History and School History Compilation Committee, *Mure Village History* (Vol. 1), pp. 419–420, 817. == See Also ==
