'''Kōshinzuka Kofun''' (庚申塚古墳) is a {{ill|Keyhole-shaped Kofun|ja|前方後円墳|lt=Zenpokoenfun|1=Zenpokoenfun|comment=doing this because I need to differentiate it in piped links too with my new interwiki tool as not the ambiguous phrase keyhole shaped kofun|1=Zenpokoenfun|1=Zenpokoenfun|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Keyhole-shaped Kofun|13=User:Immanuelle/Zenpokoenfun|qq=}} located in {{ill|Iizuna Town|ja|飯綱町|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Iizuna Town|qq=}}, {{ill|Nagano Prefecture|ja|長野県|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nagano Prefecture|qq=}}.

The mound is named "Kōshinzuka" because an ancient {{ill|Kōshin-tō|ja|庚申塔|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kōshin-tō|qq=}} was enshrined on it. In [[1933]] (Showa 8), Eiji Kuriiwa conducted an investigation and identified the site as a keyhole-shaped Kofun.

The mound, believed to have been constructed in the early {{ill|5th century|ja|5世紀|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/5th century|qq=}}, yielded burial goods including gri11ed {{ill|Haniwa|ja|埴輪|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Haniwa|qq=}} (cylindrical Haniwa), marking it as the sixth example of such finds in Japan.

== Overview ==

* type: {{ill|Keyhole-shaped Kofun|ja|前方後円墳|lt=Zenpokoenfun|1=Zenpokoenfun|comment=doing this because I need to differentiate it in piped links too with my new interwiki tool as not the ambiguous phrase keyhole shaped kofun|1=Zenpokoenfun|1=Zenpokoenfun|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Keyhole-shaped Kofun|13=User:Immanuelle/Zenpokoenfun|qq=}}
* area:
** Total length: approx. 52m
** Rear circle diameter: approx. 31m
** Rear circle height: 3.5m
** Front projection width: approx. 15–17m
** Front projection height: 1.5m

<gallery widths="200px">
庚申塚古墳２.jpg|Close view of Kōshinzuka Kofun
庚申塚古墳３.jpg|Stone monument
庚申塚古墳４.jpg|Kōshin-tō
</gallery>

== location ==

* Nagano Prefecture, Kamiminochi District, {{ill|Iizuna Town|ja|飯綱町|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Iizuna Town|qq=}}, Hirade, Nishinura 1007-1, 1008-1

== Transportation Access ==

* Nearest Station: {{ill|Shinano Railway|ja|しなの鉄道|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shinano Railway|qq=}} {{ill|Mure Station|ja|牟礼駅|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Mure Station|qq=}} (Approx. 8 minutes by car)

== References ==

* Mure Village History and School History Compilation Committee, *Mure Village History* (Vol. 1), pp. 419–420, 817.
